</p>

<p class="fnline"><a class="footnotebody" href="anonymous-the-anarchism-of-the-other-person#fn_back23" id="fn23">[23]</a> Because gender is such an important problem in Levinas and throughout philosophy, I will use masculine pronouns to discuss human persons and neuter pronouns for abstractions, but will try not to masquerade this issue by alternating with feminine pronouns.
</p>

